flowchart TB
    N1["1. Technical objective: Observes SOL bridge events and turns them into normalized Neo N4 relay messages."]
    N2["2. Determinism: same source-chain event maps to one replay-protected bridge message"]
    N3["3. Input constraints: SOL RPC/log stream | bridge contract events | checkpoint cursor"]
    N4["4. Transition rule: events become normalized messages and then asset/state actions"]
    N5["5. Verifiable output: relay job | audit log | health metric"]
    N6["6. Minimal trust: trust confirmation and verification rules, not one watcher or RPC endpoint"]
    N7["7. Layer separation: watching, message normalization, asset state, and final verification are separated"]
    N8["8. Observable evidence: source event, confirmations, message hash, cursor, submit hash, and final state"]
    N1 --> N2
    N1 --> N3
    N1 --> N4
    N1 --> N5
    N1 --> N6
    N1 --> N7
    N1 --> N8
    N2 -. constrains .-> N4
    N4 -. produces .-> N5
    N5 -. consumed by .-> N6
    classDef core fill:#0f172a,stroke:#38bdf8,color:#e5f2ff,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef support fill:#111827,stroke:#64748b,color:#f8fafc;
    class N1 core;
    class N2,N3,N4,N5,N6,N7,N8 support;
